  description:
    en: "Assumed share of type of efficiency programme for lever - Energy carrier:
      electricity - Efficiency programme: minor_improvements - UUID: 53e3a91f-eb90-4dc1-ad22-1799bd50ed04
      - 2030: 0 - 2051: 0 - Metric: Assumed share of type of efficiency programme
      for lever - Valencia forecast assumption - 2030<br/>Assumed share of type of
      efficiency programme for lever - Energy carrier: electricity - Efficiency programme:
      aggressive_improvements - UUID: 577bf77b-825e-43ac-a210-cb2653dc6983 - 2030:
      1 - 2051: 1 - Metric: Assumed share of type of efficiency programme for lever
      - Valencia forecast assumption - 2030<br/>Building costs - new buildings - Building
      energy class: new_standard - 2023: 1074.0 - Metric: Building costs - new buildings
      - ZEBRA2020, \"Deliverable 5.1: nZEB technology solutions, cost assessment and
      performance\", https://www.zebra2020.eu/website/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/Zebra2020_Deliverable-5.1_Report.pdf<br/>Building
      costs - new buildings - Building energy class: new_top_performance - 2023: 1222.33332
      - Metric: Building costs - new buildings - ZEBRA2020, \"Deliverable 5.1: nZEB
      technology solutions, cost assessment and performance\", https://www.zebra2020.eu/website/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/Zebra2020_Deliverable-5.1_Report.pdf<br/>Cost
      of energy renovations - Cost type: infrastructure_costs - Building energy class:
      minor_renovation - 2023: 56.70397678 - Metric: Cost of energy renovations -
      BPIE (2011) - \"Europe's buildings under the microscope\". http://bpie.eu/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/HR_EU_B_under_microscope_study.pdf<br/>Cost
      of energy renovations - Cost type: infrastructure_costs - Building energy class:
      major_renovation - 2023: 124.9267365 - Metric: Cost of energy renovations -
      BPIE (2011) - \"Europe's buildings under the microscope\". http://bpie.eu/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/HR_EU_B_under_microscope_study.pdf<br/>building
      renovation investments - Cost type: infrastructure_costs - Stakeholder: citizens
      - 2023: 0.7 - Metric: building renovation investments - According to the ECV,
      the proportion of renting households in 2018 amounted to 23.6% in Madrid. Cities
      own some buildings. Assume investments are made by the owner<br/>building renovation
      investments - Cost type: infrastructure_costs - Stakeholder: property_owners
      - 2023: 0.25 - Metric: building renovation investments - Do we need to confirm
      with cities?<br/>building renovation investments - Cost type: infrastructure_costs
      - Stakeholder: cities - 2023: 0.05 - Metric: building renovation investments
      - Yes<br/>building renovation investments - Cost type: infrastructure_costs
      - Stakeholder: transport_operators - 2023: 0.0 - Metric: building renovation
      investments - Source: https://www.bde.es/f/webbde/SES/Secciones/Publicaciones/InformesBoletinesRevistas/ArticulosAnaliticos/19/T3/descargar/Files/be1903-art25e.pdf<br/>investment
      costs in new buildings - Cost type: capex - Stakeholder: citizens - 2023: 0.3
      - Metric: investment costs in new buildings - Property owners stand for a larger
      amount of up front investments in new buildings given its often a property developer
      that pays. These costs are eventually distributed through Yeser prices for apartments/houses
      and Yeser rents, which is not reflected here. Cities will take part of this
      cost through Noer land prices<br/>investment costs in new buildings - Cost type:
      capex - Stakeholder: property_owners - 2023: 0.6 - Metric: investment costs
      in new buildings - Do we need to confirm with cities?<br/>investment costs in
      new buildings - Cost type: capex - Stakeholder: cities - 2023: 0.1 - Metric:
      investment costs in new buildings - Yes<br/>Materials as share of total mass
      - Material: concrete - 2023: 0.4171748531 - Metric: Materials as share of total
      mass - http://ec.europa.eu/environment/eussd/pdf/Resource%20efficiency%20in%20the%20building%20sector.pdf<br/>Tonnes
      material used for renovations - Building energy class: minor_renovation - 2023:
      0.06135046777 - Metric: Tonnes material used for renovations - Material Economics
      analysis in The Circular Economy (2018)<br/>Tonnes material used for renovations
      - Building energy class: moderate_renovation - 2023: 0.9202570166 - Metric:
      Tonnes material used for renovations - Material Economics analysis in The Circular
      Economy (2018)<br/>Tonnes material used for renovations - Building energy class:
      major_renovation - 2023: 1.840514033 - Metric: Tonnes material used for renovations
      - Material Economics analysis in The Circular Economy (2018)<br/>Tonnes material
      used for renovations - Building energy class: nzeb - 2023: 2.76077105 - Metric:
      Tonnes material used for renovations - Material Economics analysis in The Circular
      Economy (2018)<br/>Production costs per tonne - Material: concrete - 2023: 15.3
      - Metric: Production costs per tonne - Material Economics (2019) - Industrial
      Transformation 2050. Pathways to Net-Zero Emissions from EU Heavy Industry<br/>Production
      costs per tonne - Material: steel - 2023: 547.0 - Metric: Production costs per
      tonne - Material Economics (2019) - Industrial Transformation 2050. Pathways
      to Net-Zero Emissions from EU Heavy Industry<br/>Production costs per tonne
      - Material: plastics - 2023: 1242.0 - Metric: Production costs per tonne - Material
      Economics (2019) - Industrial Transformation 2050. Pathways to Net-Zero Emissions
      from EU Heavy Industry<br/>Jobs created by investment in renovation - 2023:
      18.0 - Metric: Jobs created by investment in renovation - Source: Cuchi & Sweatman
      (2011); A NATIONAL PERSPECTIVE ON SPAIN’S BUILDINGS SECTOR A ROADMAP FOR A NEW
      HOUSING SECTOR<br/>Cost of efficiency programme per m2 - Cost type: capex -
      Energy carrier: electricity - Efficiency programme: minor_improvements - 2023:
      6.5 - Metric: Cost of efficiency programme per m2 - Dinh et. al. (2013). Energy
      Efficiency Potential of the European Building Stock. Based on assumed cost of
      replacing one light bulb of 7€ and that buildings on average have one light
      bulb per 12 m2<br/>Cost of efficiency programme per m2 - Cost type: capex -
      Energy carrier: electricity - Efficiency programme: aggressive_improvements
      - 2023: 24.26 - Metric: Cost of efficiency programme per m2 - Dinh et. al. (2013).
      Energy Efficiency Potential of the European Building Stock. Based on assumed
      cost of €500 per appliance"
